title: Adam Ruins Giving
subtitle: Adam Ruins Giving
shortDescription: Tonight, host Adam Conover dispels widespread misconceptions about everything from diamond engagement rings to canned goods.

title: Adam Ruins Security
subtitle: Adam Ruins Security
shortDescription: Adam sets his sights on security theater, explaining that airport security wastes too much of our time and money, medicine safety seals do nothing to protect us, and your credit card number isn't remotely secure.

title: Adam Ruins Cars
subtitle: Adam Ruins Cars
shortDescription: Adam dives into the much-beloved auto industry and exposes the surprising truths behind car dealerships, car ownership and the concept of "jaywalking."

title: Adam Ruins Forensic Science
subtitle: Adam Ruins Forensic Science
shortDescription: Adam Ruins Forensic Science: Adam uncovers the scary truth behind unreliable methods used to build evidence in criminal cases - which often send innocent people to jail.

title: Adam Ruins Restaurants
subtitle: Adam Ruins Restaurants
shortDescription: Adam dives deep into the hidden truths of dining out. He explains why tipping we'd be better off without, experts can't tell the difference between wines, and reveals fraudulently labeled seafood is rampant.

title: Adam Ruins Hygiene
subtitle: Adam Ruins Hygiene
shortDescription: Adam reveals that the term halitosis was popularized in a 1920s ad campaign that used cruel ads to make people insecure about their breath, and explains why running water is one of the greatest miracles of the modern age.

title: Adam Ruins Voting
subtitle: Adam Ruins Voting
shortDescription: Adam explores the twisted history of the Electoral College, explaining that the Founding Fathers did not want most Americans to vote. He also takes a stab at fixing a political system that seems rigged against True democracy.

title: Adam Ruins Work
subtitle: Adam Ruins Work
shortDescription: Adam shows how the 40-hour work week not only exhausts employees but also arms businesses, reveals the legal mess of hiring interns and freelancers, and explores how discussing your salary with co-workers is actually a good thing.

title: Adam Ruins Summer Fun
subtitle: Adam Ruins Summer Fun
shortDescription: Adam crashes the last day of summer by revealing extended vacations makes you dumber, and Mickey Mouse has made a mess of our copyright laws. Adam also unveils a surprising gender bias in the world of videogames.

title: Adam Ruins Sex
subtitle: Adam Ruins Sex
shortDescription: Adam reveals that circumcision was popularized by a bunch of masturbation-curbing 19th century prudes. Plus, he reveals why the fear of having herpes is overblown and explores why the term "pop your cherry" is a bunch of nonsense.

title: Adam Ruins Nutrition
subtitle: Adam Ruins Nutrition
shortDescription: Adam shows why vitamin supplements don't make us any healthier, and that the "balanced breakfast" we've been sold is anything but. Later, he reveals how most of the nutritional science the media reports on isn't science at all.

title: Adam Ruins Death
subtitle: Adam Ruins Death
shortDescription: Adam explains the end is inevitable, shows why immortality is a fantasy and reveals that the American funeral industry is a racket that exploits mourners' grief and fear of dying.

title: Adam Ruins Hollywood
subtitle: Adam Ruins Hollywood
shortDescription: Straight from the red carpet, with help from celebrity guests Rachel Bloom and Ariana Madix, Adam exposes the hidden truths behind Hollywood's glitz and glamour, from the clothes stars wear to the process behind movie ratings.

title: Adam Ruins Football
subtitle: Adam Ruins Football
shortDescription: Adam hits the gridiron to explain why the playoffs rarely determine which team is best, and then explores how hydration myths spread by sports drink companies put kids at risk. Adam also tackles football-caused brain injuries.

title: Adam Ruins Weddings
subtitle: Adam Ruins Weddings
shortDescription: Emily and Murph's wedding day is here but Adam's gift of information may rain on their parade. Adam reveals how most wedding traditions were recently created by consumerism, and divorce is actually a wonderful thing.

title: Adam Ruins Shopping Malls
subtitle: Adam Ruins Shopping Malls
shortDescription: Adam and Emily go on a shopping spree of knowledge and find that malls were created as tax loopholes, nutrient supplements are often unregulated, and most eyeglasses are made by one manufacturer that inflates its prices.

title: Adam Ruins Animals
subtitle: Adam Ruins Animals
shortDescription: Adam explores how purebred dogs are genetic monsters created by bored Victorians, domestic cats are overpopulated killing machines that threaten other animals and wild animal trophy hunting can actually help endangered species.

title: Adam Ruins Immigration
subtitle: Adam Ruins Immigration
shortDescription: Adam illustrates how a border wall wouldn't keep out legal immigrants who overstay their visas, racist mass deportations have historically led to disaster, and immigration courts are a huge mess.

title: Adam Ruins Housing
subtitle: Adam Ruins Housing
shortDescription: Adam gets evicted from his home, and while searching for a new place, he exposes the harsh realities of real estate. Plus, Adam explains why helping the homeless is a lot simpler and more straightforward than you might think.

title: Adam Ruins Drugs
subtitle: Adam Ruins Drugs
shortDescription: Adam weeds through the misconceptions of marijuana and exposes the blunt truth about the War on Drugs. It stemmed from a racist and political agenda. Plus, Adam illustrates why prescription pills are the True gateway drug.

title: Adam Ruins Prison
subtitle: Adam Ruins Prison
shortDescription: When Emily gets tossed in the slammer, her cellmate reveals corporations make money off prison inmates while the system does nothing to reduce crime. Adam then sheds light on jail rehabilitation and solitary confinement.

title: Adam Ruins the Wild West
subtitle: Adam Ruins the Wild West
shortDescription: Adam reveals how prostitution, despite its reputation, actually helped settle the West. He then explains why the All-American Cowboy is a myth and the real western hero wasn't a person. It was air conditioning.

title: Adam Ruins Justice
subtitle: Adam Ruins Justice
shortDescription: After getting Emily out of prison, Adam and his sister Rhea take on the Justice system, showing that juries simply can't be impartial and the prosecution team is way better and well funded than your court appointed lawyer.

title: Adam Ruins Christmas
subtitle: Adam Ruins Christmas
shortDescription: Ho ho huh?! Adam teaches his sister that the real St. Nick story is a lot creepier than she thought, and modern Santa was created by commercialism only a century ago. Adam also reveals how gift-giving actually hurts the economy.

title: Adam Ruins Going Green
subtitle: Adam Ruins Going Green
shortDescription: Adam meets a young dad on a personal mission to save the world and end climate change until Adam turns his world upside down. Find out why electric cars and green products don't make the impact you've been promised.

title: Adam Ruins Having a Baby
subtitle: Adam Ruins Having a Baby
shortDescription: Adam dispels the myth about getting pregnant after 35, delves into breastfeeding vs formula, and explores postpartum depression for women - and men.

title: Adam Ruins Weight Loss
subtitle: Adam Ruins Weight Loss
shortDescription: Host Adam Conover illustrates all the reasons low-fat diets can actually make you fatter, and why counting calories is a waste of time.

title: Adam Ruins the Hospital
subtitle: Adam Ruins the Hospital
shortDescription: Adam Conover explains that inflated hospital costs have created a system that's unaffordable and unfair. Plus, the reckless prescription of antibiotics is making them worthless, and you might not need a mammogram.

title: Adam Ruins Dating
subtitle: Adam Ruins Dating
shortDescription: Adam swipes right on knowledge by exposing the flaws in dating sites. Plus, alpha males (and wolves) don't exist, and personality tests are a failure.

title: Adam Ruins Art
subtitle: Adam Ruins Art
shortDescription: Adam shows why popular art is revered, regardless of merit. He also exposes the masters as copycats and reveals the art market to be a moneymaking scheme.

title: Adam Ruins What We Learned in School
subtitle: Adam Ruins What We Learned in School
shortDescription: In his first animated episode, Adam teaches a crew of kids and their teacher that Christopher Columbus didn't discover America, King Tut was a dud, and the rules of grammar are not as ironclad as you'd think.

title: Adam Ruins College
subtitle: Adam Ruins College
shortDescription: Adam explains why the odds of becoming a dropout billionaire are not in your favor, how manipulated school rankings have little to do with education quality and why the privatization of student loans created a massive debt crisis.

title: Emily Ruins Adam
subtitle: Emily Ruins Adam
shortDescription: Emily takes over to "ruin" Adam, pointing out where his facts fall short. She debunks the idea that IQ tests measure intelligence and points to information Adam has gotten wrong in the past. Plus, she explains the "backfire effect."

title: Adam Ruins His Vacation
subtitle: Adam Ruins His Vacation
shortDescription: Get ready for some R&R (Ruining and more Ruining!), as Adam Conover and his girlfriend take a journey across America.

title: Adam Ruins the Suburbs
subtitle: Adam Ruins the Suburbs
shortDescription: Adam explains that your lawn is an unnatural monstrosity, suburban design is killing you, and the racist past of suburbs led to segregation in schools.

title: Adam Ruins The Economy
subtitle: Adam Ruins The Economy
shortDescription: Adam explains why doing taxes is unnecessarily complicated, the economic numbers we hear don't reveal much, and American manufacturing can't return.

title: Adam Ruins Conspiracy Theories
subtitle: Adam Ruins Conspiracy Theories
shortDescription: Adam Conover debunks the fake moon landing theory, discusses the Satanic Panic of the 1980s and reveals how to spot a False theory.

title: Adam Ruins Spa Day
subtitle: Adam Ruins Spa Day
shortDescription: Pricey detox treatments may do more harm than good, MSG's scary reputation is undeserved, and the placebo effect is way more powerful than you think!

title: Adam Ruins Halloween
subtitle: Adam Ruins Halloween
shortDescription: Strangers with poisoned candy don't exist, the panic over Orson Welles' War of the Worlds broadcast didn't happen and mediums are total frauds.

title: Adam Ruins Science
subtitle: Adam Ruins Science
shortDescription: Testing on mice is a waste, and scarce funding stops scientists from seeking cures and proving their findings.

title: Adam Ruins the Future
subtitle: Adam Ruins the Future
shortDescription: Unregulated food expiration dates lead to massive waste, your 401(k) won't be enough to support your retirement and the future is unpredictable.

title: Give Me Liberty or Give Me Truth
subtitle: Give Me Liberty or Give Me Truth
shortDescription: Reanimated History: Adam Conover undermines everything you thought you knew about the American Revolution.

title: The First Factsgiving
subtitle: The First Factsgiving
shortDescription: Reanimated History: The Pilgrims were grave robbers, Pocahontas and John Smith's romance never happened, and huge cities in the New World existed before its "discovery."

title: Mutually Assured Ruination
subtitle: Mutually Assured Ruination
shortDescription: Reanimated History: The Cuban Missile Crisis was started by the US, a female politician stood up to McCarthy, and a mistake actually brought down the Berlin Wall.

title: An Ancient History of Violence
subtitle: An Ancient History of Violence
shortDescription: Reanimated History: Gladiators were barred from killing opponents, one Celtic woman nearly brought down the Romans, and the brave "300" Spartans were really 7000.

title: The Copernican Ruin-aissance
subtitle: The Copernican Ruin-aissance
shortDescription: Reanimated History: Adam sheds some light on Copernicus, a rogue dwarf revolutionized what we know about the human body, and wait until you hear about Tulip Mania!

title: 100 Years Ago Today
subtitle: 100 Years Ago Today
shortDescription: Reanimated History: Adam digs into the Panama Canal, death by food, and the even deadlier Spanish Flu.

title: Adam Ruins Guns
subtitle: Adam Ruins Guns
shortDescription: Adam Conover is back to take aim at critics on both sides of the gun debate in America. He explains why an assault weapons ban would not be effective and demonstrates how the Second Amendment has been twisted to fit the NRA's agenda.

title: Adam Ruins Sleep
subtitle: Adam Ruins Sleep
shortDescription: Adam Conover has a rude awakening for everything you thought you knew about sleep (or lack of it), from the mattress industry to supposedly lazy teens to sleep aids.

title: Adam Ruins Tech
subtitle: Adam Ruins Tech
shortDescription: Adam Conover downloads you on how the tech industry isn't really as helpful as you think - or wants you to think.

title: Adam Ruins Flying
subtitle: Adam Ruins Flying
shortDescription: Adam causes turbulence when he reveals that reward miles drive up costs, and revisits the "golden age" of air travel to uncover smoky, sexist death traps in the sky. Plus, airline mergers are crippling smaller cities.

title: Adam Ruins a Plate of Nachos
subtitle: Adam Ruins a Plate of Nachos
shortDescription: Adam dishes out the facts on the avocado trade being ruled by drug cartels, and Big Pork making bacon a pop culture hit while covering up its huge health risks. Plus, America's food problems stem from corn.

title: Adam Ruins a Sitcom
subtitle: Adam Ruins a Sitcom
shortDescription: Adam tackles classic television stereotypes, from the racism behind public pools, to the "model minority" myth of Asian Americans, to the on-screen toxic masculinity that's masking the problems young men face today.

title: Adam Ruins Games
subtitle: Adam Ruins Games
shortDescription: Adam hits pause on the myth that connects video games to real-life violence, and reveals that Monopoly was a rip-off of an anti-capitalist teaching game. Plus, Olympic organizers get rich while athletes struggle to get by.

title: Adam Ruins Nature
shortDescription: Adam digs up the dirt on nature, revealing that Mount Everest is a frozen pile of poop, natural disasters are actually man-made, and there is no such thing as untouched wilderness.

subtitle: Adam Ruins America
shortDescription: Adam lets his freedom flag fly by examining why America doesn't have higher rates of social mobility. He then uncovers the flaws within our constitution and examines our country's progression and regression.

title: Adam Ruins a Night Out
subtitle: Adam Ruins a Night Out
shortDescription: Adam and Emily prepare for a big night out by revealing the marketing ploy that led to women shaving and the fashion agendas that created pockets. Then, the two friends pour back the truth on alcohol consumption.

title: Adam Ruins Doing Good
subtitle: Adam Ruins Doing Good
shortDescription: Adam takes down the do-gooders and reveals how Teach For America is harmful to both students and teachers. He then uncovers the ineffectiveness of recycling and calls out the billionaires who create charities for tax breaks.

title: Adam Ruins a Murder
subtitle: Adam Ruins a Murder
shortDescription: Adam shines a headlight on why drivers are rarely prosecuted for car accidents that result in death. He breaks down border patrol's problematic search policies and examines the messed-up history of corpses and medical studies.

title: Adam Ruins Music
subtitle: Adam Ruins Music
shortDescription: It's time to face the music, as Adam reveals the racism behind rock & roll's origins and the egregious fees of Live Nation's monopoly. He then defends musicians who "sell out" to make a living in today's digital landscape.

title: Adam Ruins Little Bugs
subtitle: Adam Ruins Little Bugs
shortDescription: Don't let Adam's facts bug you as he uncovers the benefits of spiders, serves up knowledge on why we should be eating more bugs as a protein source, and illustrates the benefits of little bugs on your gut health.

title: Adam Ruins Cops
subtitle: Adam Ruins Cops
shortDescription: Adam polices the truth behind the overuse of SWAT Teams, illustrates how using school officers can create a pipeline for prisons, and examines the origins and intended purpose of police officers.

title: Adam Ruins Himself
subtitle: Adam Ruins Himself
shortDescription: In the season finale, Adam battles with his inner self-doubt over how biases affect the show. He then exposes the shortcomings of story-telling, and the influence (or lack thereof) of advertising on the series' integrity.

subtitle: On the Hot Seat (Explicit)

subtitle: Cop Wars (Explicit)

subtitle: A New Hope (Explicit)

subtitle: Training Day (Explicit)

subtitle: Adam Ruins Sex

subtitle: Adam Ruins Having a Baby
shortDescription: Adam dispels the myth about getting pregnant after 35, delves into breastfeeding vs formula, and explores postpartum depression for women - and men.

shortDescription: Host Adam Conover illustrates all the reasons low-fat diets can actually make you fatter, and why counting calories is a waste of time.

title: Camping
subtitle: Camping
shortDescription: Jon Glaser sets out to make a TV show about his greatest passion: gear. Along with his designated gear expert, Steve Cirbus, Jon goes on a couples camping trip but when things get weird between the couples, it threatens to derail the show.

title: Cycling
subtitle: Cycling
shortDescription: Comedian Jon Glaser takes on cycling for the next episode of his gear show, but gets sidetracked when his e-sidekick, Gear-i, writes an epic script about a post-apocalyptic bike messenger. Michael Shannon and Janeane Garofalo guest star.

title: Hockey
subtitle: Hockey
shortDescription: Jon Glaser loves hockey. But the fact that he never learned to skate until he was an adult sends him on a collision course of emotions involving his mommy and his son. Former NHL great Ron Duguay guest stars.

title: Dogs
subtitle: Dogs
shortDescription: Man's best friend deserves the best gear. But when Jon's gear show is interrupted by a neighborhood dog owner who doesn't clean up his pup's poop, Jon comes up with a plan to exact his revenge.

title: Fishing
subtitle: Fishing
shortDescription: Jon hasn't fished much - however, he's very excited to enjoy all the sweet gear. But a relaxing fishing excursion soon turns into a crushing torrent of anxiety that leaves Jon's psyche battered. Pro bass fisherman Woo Daves guest stars.

title: Baseball
subtitle: Baseball
shortDescription: Former high school baseballer Jon Glaser gives back by coaching a Little League team, but a mysterious voice turns his field of dreams into a dark journey through his past. Robert Kelly guest stars.

title: Surfing
subtitle: Surfing
shortDescription: Jon Glaser gears up for his first ever surfing lesson. But when some sweet hang time with his fake wife and his new beach bros turns into an epic wipeout, Jon ditches his surfboard for a metal detector, and gets more than he bargained for.

title: Space
subtitle: Space
shortDescription: Jon takes one giant leap for gearkind as he prepares to head to space! That is, until Jon's last meal on earth thrusts him into a psychological battle with a cold-blooded killer. MMA legend, Renzo Gracie guest stars.

title: Leisure
subtitle: Leisure
shortDescription: With his real family away, Jon decides to film in his real home and kick back in the "chill zone" with his bros. But when they all bail, Jon is left scrambling to salvage his weekend. Will gear save Jon from two days of loneliness?

title: Sailing
subtitle: Sailing
shortDescription: In this season finale, Jon sets sail for a high seas adventure, only to find himself cast adrift in a massive existential crisis. Embarking on his most extensive journey yet, Jon looks for answers to the age-old question - why gear?

title: Survival
shortDescription: When the network tells Jon it wants his 'Spurt to be the new host of the show, Jon comes up with a devious plan to oust him. Jon then visits a barbershop, tattoo parlor, and CrossFit gym to prove that he's just as macho as his old sidekick.

subtitle: Football

title: Golf
subtitle: Golf

title: Basketball
subtitle: Basketball

subtitle: Road Trip

title: Photography
subtitle: Photography
shortDescription: Jon rekindles a long-held passion for photography. But when seemingly innocent professional portraits awaken him to a personal proclivity, he becomes exposed to a whole new world and finds his True calling.

subtitle: Swing Dancing
shortDescription: Jon begrudgingly goes swing dancing with his wife Leslie, which opens a Pandora's gear box full of formerly hated couples' activities, culminating in some extremely intimate moments.

subtitle: Gearing
shortDescription: Jon's wife Leslie confronts him about his gear hoarding, which inspires him to create a brand new activity: gearing! As Jon spirals further into gear addiction, his loved ones stage an intervention. But will they be too late?

subtitle: Skydiving

title: The Boys Are Coming Together

subtitle: Lady and the Skamp
shortDescription: The teachers protest poor working conditions by going on strike, Shoemaker and Abbey butt heads over who's the real strike leader, and Loren and Rod tailgate the event leaving Quinn and Tammy to man the understaffed school.

shortDescription: Joe, Sal, Murr and Q lend an unhelpful hand while working at a high-tech store, then play detectives at the mall in search of perps on the loose. And tonight's loser gets the shakes while soaring high above the city.

title: Sneaking Number Twos, Going Number One
subtitle: Sneaking Number Twos, Going Number One
shortDescription: Joe, Q, Sal and Murr play a game of Put-Pocket at a grocery store, then get jumpy at the park after taking over each other's cell phones. And the loser learns that when you gotta go, you gotta go.

title: Blind Justice
subtitle: Blind Justice
shortDescription: The guys get a little punchy while giving boxing lessons, then head to the mall to share the gift of music with strangers. And when tonight's loser delivers the right speech to the wrong audience, he's the one who gets scared straight.

title: Tied and Feathered
subtitle: Tied and Feathered
shortDescription: The guys teach a crash course in sorry behavior, ask strangers to settle bizarre debates, and spread surprisingly good news at the mall. Plus, tonight's loser has his hands tied when a day at the park turns into a frightful mess.

title: Smushed
subtitle: Smushed
shortDescription: Joe, Q, Sal and Murr give a security presentation that's anything but safe, then hold hands with strangers in the park. And tonight's big loser quickly becomes an unwanted guest while clowning around at a kid's birthday party.

title: Impractical Jokers Live Punishment Special
subtitle: Impractical Jokers Live Punishment Special
shortDescription: Sal, Joe, Q and Murr celebrate 100 episodes of Impractical Jokers with a Live punishment in the heart of NYC.

title: The Big Uneasy
subtitle: The Big Uneasy
shortDescription: The guys take over New Orleans, as they steal sips from strangers' drinks at a famous bar, spin the Wheel of Voo-Doom on Bourbon Street, and crash some horse and buggy rides. Then, tonight's loser turns into a legendary swamp monster

title: Hopeless and Changeless
subtitle: Hopeless and Changeless
shortDescription: The guys head to the park asking strangers to agree with their bizarre points of view, then give classless lessons about real estate. Plus, tonight's loser finds himself in a harrowing race to the finish at the racetrack.

title: Stripped of Dignity
subtitle: Stripped of Dignity
shortDescription: The guys get a taste of babysitting while asking reluctant strangers to watch their kid, then head to the grocery store to conduct taste(less) tests with shoppers, and the loser is forced to strip for the wrong people.

title: The Taunted House
subtitle: The Taunted House
shortDescription: The guys get extra cheesy at a pizza parlor, then head to Wall Street where they ask strangers to help translate bizarre text messages in Spanish. And trapped in a haunted house, a nightmare comes to life for tonight's big loser.

title: Doomed
subtitle: Doomed
shortDescription: Joe, Q, Sal and Murr take in more than they bargained for while working at a tailor shop, then convince strangers to hand over their cell phones. And the big loser sacrifices his childhood for a punishment three months in the making.

title: HellCopter
subtitle: HellCopter
shortDescription: Joe, Sal, Murr and Q pose as unreceptive receptionists in an office waiting room, then head to a wax museum where they mingle with the stiff crowd. And in double punishment, the two losers are taken on a chopper ride from hell.

title: You're Cut Off
subtitle: You're Cut Off
shortDescription: The guys pose as employees at a copy center, conduct bizarre exit interviews for moviegoers, and then lead some very peculiar protests. Later, it's Unhappy Hour for the big loser, as he cuts off paying customers at a party.

title: Ruffled Feathers
subtitle: Ruffled Feathers
shortDescription: The guys conduct focus groups to sell their illogical inventions created by the other guys, then head to a shoe store where they get off on the wrong foot. And the big loser discovers he's more flight than fight at the zoo.

title: Stare Master
subtitle: Stare Master
shortDescription: The guys play a game of copycat at the park while babysitting kids. Then, they hit the supermarket for an epic battle of catch and release, and the loser learns that creeping around the gym is more uncomfortable than working out.

title: Bidder Loser
subtitle: Bidder Loser
shortDescription: The guys try to dig themselves out of a jam by asking strangers to help bury bizarre items, then compete to see who can cling the longest to a stranger's car. And the big loser makes a room full of enemies at an auction house.

title: The Good, the Bad and the Punished
subtitle: The Good, the Bad and the Punished
shortDescription: The guys pose as crabby NYC cab drivers, then head to the park to solicit undeserved congratulations. And in special travel punishment, the big loser plays sheriff in an old Nevada town full of outlaws.

title: Putting the P in Pool
subtitle: Putting the P in Pool
shortDescription: The guys pose as crummy cashiers at a grocery store and then head to the mall for a touching game involving laser pointers. Plus, the loser is soaked with embarrassment after making it clear to some swimmers that he's #1.

title: Statue of Limitations
subtitle: Statue of Limitations
shortDescription: The guys pose as inhospitable restaurant hosts, then beg strangers to babysit their grandfathers. Plus the longest punishment in Jokers' history.

title: Brother of the Sisterhood
subtitle: Brother of the Sisterhood
shortDescription: The guys play helpless oddballs in a waiting room, then ask grocery shoppers for cash. And the loser becomes the #1 enemy of women everywhere.

title: Dark Side of the Moon
subtitle: Dark Side of the Moon
shortDescription: The guys make passes at supermarket shoppers, then pose as reporters. And with a painfully invasive punishment, the loser is the butt of the joke.

title: Whose Phone Is Ringing?
subtitle: Whose Phone Is Ringing?
shortDescription: Joe, Sal, Q and Murr hit a bull's-eye at a clothing store, sabotage each other in a focus group, and the big loser is called upon at a book reading.

title: Centaur of Attention
subtitle: Centaur of Attention
shortDescription: Murr, Joe, Sal and Q go head-to-head in a focus group. Then they spread confusion at a bagel store before hitting all the wrong notes at the park. And, tonight's big loser gets hunted down during a humiliating walk of shame.

title: Browbeaten
subtitle: Browbeaten
shortDescription: Sal, Q, Murr and Joe take name-calling to new heights, the guys ask for bogus donations, and the big loser gets a shave that's too close for comfort.

title: The Coward
subtitle: The Coward
shortDescription: The guys show who's boss at a fast food joint, and whisper sweet nothings at a grocery store. Then, the big loser helps a cow in labor, and almost buys the farm.

title: Virtual Insanity
subtitle: Virtual Insanity
shortDescription: The guys bark up the wrong tree as employees at a pet store, then head to the market for a game that throws everything up in the air. And the big loser virtually loses his mind after entering a world he's never visited before.

title: Laundry Day
subtitle: Laundry Day
shortDescription: The guys look for partners in crime at a supermarket and throw caution to the wind as helpless romantics. And the loser has a serious wardrobe malfunction.

title: Water Torture
subtitle: Water Torture
shortDescription: Joe, Q, Sal and Murr spin a wheel and creep out shoppers at the mall. And the punishment leaves one Joker soaked, enraged, and totally shocked.

title: Hitting the Wrong Note
subtitle: Hitting the Wrong Note
shortDescription: The guys dress to the nines but act like zeroes while trying to get sympathy, and the big loser faces the music in a tone-deaf punishment.

title: Heckle and Hide
subtitle: Heckle and Hide
shortDescription: The guys ask strangers for a little help with big items at the grocery store, and give entrepreneurial tips to some unfortunate souls. Plus, the big loser strikes out at a little league softball game while posing as that dad.

title: The Chairman
subtitle: The Chairman
shortDescription: The guys shock shoppers by going footloose and fancy-free in a discount store, then pose insane questions to strangers in the park. And the big loser is taken for a wild ride in a tricked-out wheelchair he can't possibly control.

title: Wrapper's Delight
subtitle: Wrapper's Delight
shortDescription: The guys make a mockery of each other as restaurant managers, name that (made up) tune with strangers, and then head to the park for some awkward fun in the sun. Plus, the big loser gets wrapped up in a birthday surprise.

title: Ash Clown
subtitle: Ash Clown
shortDescription: The guys give customers an eye-opening experience at a glasses store, and then convince grocery shoppers to pass ridiculous messages while shopping. Plus, the loser gives back at a Career Day assembly that's divorced from reality.

title: Spider Man
subtitle: Spider Man
shortDescription: Sal, Murr, Joe and Q give all-you-can eat buffet customers all they can handle, and turn into real power tools while teaching workshops at a hardware store. Then, tonight's big loser suffers a punishment that will make your skin crawl.

title: Stage Fright
subtitle: Stage Fright
shortDescription: The guys serve up raw deals while working the counter at a pawn shop and try to convince strangers in the park to give them hugs after incredibly bizarre apologies. Then, the big loser performs his own life story through song.

title: Training Day
shortDescription: Joe, Sal, Murr and Q show up to a supermarket with bells on, and then it's dj vu in the park as the guys try to reminisce with total strangers. And later, the three big losers are put through an epic trial by fire.

title: Impractical Jokers Live: Nitro Circus Spectacular
subtitle: Impractical Jokers Live: Nitro Circus Spectacular
shortDescription: The Impractical Jokers team with Nitro Circus feature obstacle courses, high-flying jumps and a punishment unlike anything you've seen before.

title: NCAA March Madness Showdown
subtitle: NCAA March Madness Showdown
shortDescription: The guys compete bracket style and go head-to-head, pitting their best moments against each other. 16 clips start, but only one will prevail.

title: Swim Shady
subtitle: Swim Shady
shortDescription: Joe, Sal, Murr and Q hit some bad reception while working a desk, and then head to a park to ask strangers for advice on their questionable life choices. Plus, tonight's loser goes to a water aerobics class, but ends up drowning in shame.

title: Lady and the Tramp
subtitle: Lady and the Tramp
shortDescription: Q, Sal, Murr and Joe use a two-way mirror to get each other to crack, and then hit a grocery to see who can sell the most samples. Plus, tonight's loser gets taken for a ride that ends with a visit to the Statue of Liberty.

title: The Parent Trap
subtitle: The Parent Trap
shortDescription: Sal, Joe, Murr and Q get stuck in a grocery showdown, beg strangers for questionable quotes, and spew financial tips that are anything but sound. Plus, tonight's loser earns a time-out for his outrageous antics at a kid's play space.

title: Catastrophe
subtitle: Catastrophe
shortDescription: Murr, Sal, Q and Joe serve up the goods posing as trainees at a juice bar and plead with strangers to get things untangled. Plus, tonight's big loser confronts his biggest fear in a punishment that leaves him practically catatonic.

title: Vampire Weakened
subtitle: Vampire Weakened
shortDescription: Sal, Joe, Murr and Q act frosty while working the ice cream counter, then take Joe's dogs for a romp in the park with help from some strangers. Later, tonight's loser watches his blood boil while performing with a gospel choir.

title: Footlose
subtitle: Footlose
shortDescription: Joe, Murr, Q and Sal call out odd names while working at an office. Later, the guys ask park-goers for help with online dating profiles. And tonight's loser fails to keep his cool while getting up close and personal with some strange feet.

title: X Man
subtitle: X Man
shortDescription: Q, Sal, Murr and Joe compete in their first four-way challenge. Plus, see what happens when the guys try to lead a kid's art class, and find out which joker fails so badly, he's hit with an on-the-spot punishment that leaves him seeing red.

title: Medium, Well Done
subtitle: Medium, Well Done
shortDescription: Murr, Sal, Q and Joe climb the corporate ladder as TV execs pitching insane show ideas, and tonight's big loser bares his soul while undergoing a humiliating psychic reading that puts his real life on the wrong track.

title: Drum and Drummer
subtitle: Drum and Drummer
shortDescription: Sal, Murr, Q and Joe convince shoppers to repeat bizarre catch phrases, then go mental while psychoanalyzing strangers. Plus, it's an awkward drum roll for tonight's pair of losers when they're forced to perform at a halftime show.

title: The Butt of the Joker
subtitle: The Butt of the Joker
shortDescription: Sal, Q, Joe and Murr are partners in focus group presentations, supporting one another's insane ideas on living life to the fullest. And tonight's loser tries to cure the public of a nasty habit - but gets people smoking mad.

title: Stuffed Turkey
subtitle: Stuffed Turkey
shortDescription: Q, Sal, Joe and Murr act as not-so-handy-men, helping strangers assemble furniture. The guys pair up for a panty drop at the mall, and Thanksgiving comes early for tonight's loser when he's forced to talk turkey at a dating event.

title: Crickets
subtitle: Crickets
shortDescription: It's hats off for Murr, Sal, Q and Joe when they work as cap salesmen. Then, the guys head to Joey Fatone's hot dog joint to serve confused customers. And tonight's loser performs a stand-up comedy routine but barely gets out alive.

title: Universal Appeal
subtitle: Universal Appeal
shortDescription: Q, Sal, Murr and Joe invade Orlando! The guys are out of line managing a ride at a theme park, then get all wet on a river adventure, and man the (mis)information booth. Plus, tonight's loser goes from spider hero to barnyard zero.

title: Paradise Lost
subtitle: Paradise Lost
shortDescription: Sal, Murr, Joe and Q say "aloha" in a fun Hawaiian episode! The future looks hazy when the guys pose as fortune tellers and practice indecent proposals at a romantic waterfall. Plus, it's blood in the water for the big loser.

title: Mime and Punishment
subtitle: Mime and Punishment
shortDescription: Joe, Sal, Murr and Q put the nasty in namaste when they lead guided meditations that leave their victims with a lot to think about. And the big loser gets boxed in with the very first 24-hour punishment.

title: Three Men and Your Baby
subtitle: Three Men and Your Baby
shortDescription: Sal, Joe, Murr and Q get snap happy while posing as photographers, then ask strangers for help filling out forms. And all but one of the guys are faced with a punishment that's not child's play.

title: The Q-Pay
subtitle: The Q-Pay
shortDescription: Q, Murr, Sal and Joe share TMI texts and sabotage each other at a dating event. Plus, tonight's loser gets a special donation that he must wear all season long.

title: Rubbed the Wrong Way
subtitle: Rubbed the Wrong Way
shortDescription: The guys send odd texts and throw caution (and groceries) to the wind. Plus, tonight's loser is cast as a genie but wishes he could be anywhere else.

title: Flatfoot the Pirate
subtitle: Flatfoot the Pirate
shortDescription: Q, Sal, Joe and Murr explain why they've been doused with water at the mall, and tonight's big loser plays a pirate but won't find any rum in his cup.

title: Remember the Pact
subtitle: Remember the Pact
shortDescription: Murr, Sal, Joe and Q beg shoppers to hold on to a weird item for them, then help teach tech to senior citizens. Plus, after a successful secret pact, tonight's loser reveals his embarrassing digital life to his own father.

title: Silence of the Lame
subtitle: Silence of the Lame
shortDescription: It's all play and no work when Sal, Murr, Q and Joe square off in a toy-pitching competition. And tonight's big loser nearly gets the shush beat out of him while trying to quiet down patrons in the food court.

title: The Walking Dread
subtitle: The Walking Dread
shortDescription: Joe, Murr, Sal and Q take time to smell the roses, then pair up to double dip at the mall. And tonight's loser battles an undead enemy to save his family.

title: Take Me Out at the Ballgame
subtitle: Take Me Out at the Ballgame
shortDescription: Q, Murr, Joe and Sal get drenched at a water park, and tonight's loser strikes out while jockeying for a ball from Mets pitcher Noah Syndergaard.

title: The Party Crasher
subtitle: The Party Crasher
shortDescription: Joe, Sal, Q and Murr dodge shakedowns with the help of some strangers, and tonight's loser has a run-in at a party that leaves him down for the count.

title: Dover and Out
subtitle: Dover and Out
shortDescription: Sal, Murr, Joe and Q survey employees with odd questions, and the loser unveils a mural in a small town whose residents react with big city rage.

title: G.I. Jokers
subtitle: G.I. Jokers
shortDescription: Sal, Joe, Murr and Q share (mis)information on aviation, and three brave vets get their own permanent punishments. Plus, a double punishment goes up in flames!

title: NCAA March Madness Bracket Attack
subtitle: NCAA March Madness Bracket Attack
shortDescription: Sal, Q, Murr and Joe pit their most uncomfortable, terrifying, dangerous and gross punishments from the history of Impractical Jokers against each other, to find out which one takes the title

title: The Marathon Man
subtitle: The Marathon Man
shortDescription: Sal, Murr, Q and Joe climb to the Top of the Rock for some awkward interactions, then "wet" appetites at a bagel shop. And the big loser suits up - or down - for a run across the Brooklyn Bridge that's anything but inspiring.

title: Guilty as Charged
subtitle: Guilty as Charged
shortDescription: Murr, Sal, Joe and Q enlist shoppers to help them avoid a security guard out to get them, and the guys get spacey while teaching about UFOs. Plus, the big loser faces the wrath of a crowd of rockers who are ready to rumble.

title: No Good Deed
subtitle: No Good Deed
shortDescription: Q, Sal, Murr and Joe compete in a focus group face-off, convincing people that their TV show ideas are the tops, and tonight's losers might get run out of town when they reveal their financial mismanagement plan to charity donors.

title: Stripteased
subtitle: Stripteased
shortDescription: Murr, Joe, Q and Sal return to the dentist's office, then try to make each other laugh in a food court tournament. And the big loser strips for a rowdy group of ladies who will never be able to un-see the sorry state of his skin.

title: Indecent Proposal
subtitle: Indecent Proposal
shortDescription: Sal, Murr, Joe and Q don absurd disguises to trick unsuspecting receptionists, then try to convince strangers to sign off on some unusual emails. Plus, the big loser turns a harmless dance class into a dance with danger.

title: Turning the Tables
subtitle: Turning the Tables
shortDescription: Sal, Joe, Murr and Q take a spin in a motorized chair hoping the kindness of strangers will keep them on track, and tonight's big loser walks away bruised and battered when he's forced to clear some tables in an unusual way.

title: Lords of the Ring
subtitle: Lords of the Ring
shortDescription: Joe, Murr, Sal and Q skirt the law while posing as receptionists, then go fishing at an unlikely locale. And the heat is on tonight's big losers as they try to give one unlucky customer the deal of a lifetime.

title: No Child Left Behind
subtitle: No Child Left Behind
shortDescription: Q, Murr, Joe and Sal pitch toys that should be kept away from tots, face off at a market (resulting in some pinched nerves), and see spots at the mall. Plus, the big loser sticks his nose where it doesn't belong.

title: Pulling the Rug
subtitle: Pulling the Rug
shortDescription: Joe, Murr, Q and Sal run a surprise challenge, and a stint at The Cake Boss's counter is anything but sweet. Then, advice for kids turns awkward when heard by strangers, and tonight's loser looks for a new 'do - but not for himself.

title: Speech Impediment
subtitle: Speech Impediment
shortDescription: Joe, Q, Sal and Murr crack each other up while performing strange scenes behind glass, then test out awkward proposals at the Top of the Rock. And the big loser gets tongue-tied while speaking before government officials.

title: Card Against Humanity
subtitle: Card Against Humanity
shortDescription: Q, Murr, Joe and Sal have customers seeing red while working at an optician's office, then get too close for comfort eavesdropping on strangers' conversations. Plus, the big loser gives the business at a networking event.

title: Bull Shiatsu
subtitle: Bull Shiatsu
shortDescription: Sal, Joe, Murr and Q try to hold it together as receptionists checking in some strange characters. Later, they offer up odd rewards to helpful strangers, and the big loser gets the stuffing squished out of him at the mall.

title: The Running of the Bullies
subtitle: The Running of the Bullies
shortDescription: Q, Murr, Joe and Sal offer up peculiar specials at a steakhouse and get creepy while helping to clean a prop house. Plus, tonight's big loser realizes he may need his own lifeguard after making waves at the pool.

title: The Needy and the Greedy
subtitle: The Needy and the Greedy
shortDescription: Joe, Murr, Q and Sal have fast fingers at a focus group and leave no cereal box unturned at the grocery store. Then, tonight's big loser opens a can of something fierce at a local donation center.

title: Washed Up
subtitle: Washed Up
shortDescription: Q, Joe, Sal and Murr rat each other out at a pizza place and get into textual relationships with strangers at the mall. Then, the big loser twerks hard for the money at an impromptu bikini car wash.

title: To Hatch a Predator
subtitle: To Hatch a Predator
shortDescription: The Jokers perform unusual methods of DNA testing and get too close for comfort at the grocery store. Then, tonight's big loser becomes a shell of a man after he cracks under pressure during a presentation at a children's museum.

title: Like a Boss
subtitle: Like a Boss
shortDescription: The Jokers act fast and furiously as employees at a theme park and go postal on model citizens who don't realize they're part of the picture. Then, tonight's big loser tumbles and falls after antagonizing a room full of Guy Fieri fans.

title: Chick Magnet
subtitle: Chick Magnet
shortDescription: The guys turn on the charm to make a restaurant basement sound enticing and recruit unsuspecting shoppers to shout out bizarre nicknames. Then, tonight's big loser must find his way out of the cuckoo's nest before the chicks get crazy!

title: Dropping Knowledge
subtitle: Dropping Knowledge
shortDescription: The guys pump the breaks on a bike ride to ask perplexed strangers for help and cut the java line to get the go-ahead on some very strange emails. Plus tonight's big loser gets schooled in a game show that barely makes the grade.

title: Hump Day
subtitle: Hump Day
shortDescription: Q, Sal, Joe and Murr Greek out while lending a hand to customers at a casual restaurant, then battle across the table of a focus group. Plus the big loser gets spitting mad when forced to spend some quality time at the zoo.

title: Out of Left Field
subtitle: Out of Left Field
shortDescription: The guys try not to crack up during a four-way face off and later find that a stroll with the Gatto pups is no walk in the park. Plus, tonight's big loser suffers more than muscle failure in a major league embarrassment.

title: Autograph Corrector
subtitle: Autograph Corrector
shortDescription: The guys rely on the kindness of strangers to help answer some awkward questions, then go looking for love in the park. Plus, tonight's big loser strikes out amongst baseball fans with an assist from Yankees legend Tino Martinez.

title: The Bogey Man
subtitle: The Bogey Man
shortDescription: The laughing gas flows freely when the guys pose as dental assistants. Later they make headlines for all the wrong reasons and get burned giving some campfire tips. Plus the big loser scores a hole in none on the links.

title: Hell on Wheels
subtitle: Hell on Wheels
shortDescription: The guys try and work out the kinks as physical therapists, then pitch some way out-of-the-box ideas for TV hosts. Plus, the big loser gets rolled over by some speedy ladies.

title: Pantsing with the Stars
subtitle: Pantsing with the Stars
shortDescription: The guys pair up to share educational ideas with perplexed parents, then teach Krav Maga to martial arts newbies. But when one Joker refuses, he becomes the big loser and faces an opponent that scares the pants off him.

title: Staten Island Holiday Spectacular
subtitle: Staten Island Holiday Spectacular
shortDescription: The guys celebrate with some unseasonable specials, followed by new toys you may not want under the tree. Then, gift wrapping goes awry, and the big loser has a close encounter with some hungry wild life.

title: The Jokers Games
subtitle: The Jokers Games
shortDescription: Get ready to judge Joe, Murr, Sal and Q on the exemplary skills (or lack thereof) that they've displayed over the years. Host Joey Fatone is joined by championship athletes, and past punishers, to see how the guys measure up.

title: March Madness Breakdown
subtitle: March Madness Breakdown
shortDescription: Tune in to find out which Joker is this year's top draft pick as determined by NBA stars Doug McDermott and Enes Kanter, along with host Joey Fatone - not an NBA star.

title: Spring Break Countdown
subtitle: Spring Break Countdown
shortDescription: Make a splash as we count down Q, Murr, Sal and Joe's most cringeworthy, embarrassing and hilarious moments of fun in the sun. Plus, you'll come away with a dozen totally ridiculous spring break tips to take with you!

title: Joker for a Day
subtitle: Joker for a Day
shortDescription: Joe, Sal, Murr, and Q surprise their crew by flipping the cameras on them in this special episode. Watch as members of the Jokers family emerge from behind the scenes to compete in classic games as their bosses egg them on.

title: Hits, Errors & Balls!
subtitle: Hits, Errors & Balls!
shortDescription: Join the guys as they count down the top 9 greatest baseball moments in Impractical Jokers history! Find out who used to be an athlete and who is often stopped by stadium security. Plus, never-before-seen bonus footage!

title: Holiday Party
subtitle: Holiday Party
shortDescription: Joe, Sal, Q and Murr invite you inside their festive shindig, alongside their beloved crew. It's one event you won't want to miss, chock-full of bonus footage, behind-the-scenes banter, and special gifts - for Sal, anyway. Plus, ham!

title: Crash Test Dummies
subtitle: Crash Test Dummies
shortDescription: Murr, Sal, Joe and Q take some customers for a wild ride, and things get messy when they ask fellow shoppers for a hand. Plus, the big losers suffer a monster punishment that leaves them crushed.

title: The Closer
subtitle: The Closer
shortDescription: Q, Joe, Sal and Murr get tech help from some confused tutors, then play Hot Potato in a shoe store. Plus, the big loser wishes he could press escape during a brutal coffee shop punishment.

title: Tipping Point
subtitle: Tipping Point
shortDescription: Sal, Murr, Joe and Q pull desk duty, and then do strangers a solid by barring them from the bathroom. Plus, the big loser learns the hard way that gratuity is not included.

title: Full Mental Jacket
subtitle: Full Mental Jacket
shortDescription: Joe, Murr, Q and Sal send blood pressure rates sky-high while posing as nurses, then stroll through the store with their wives. Plus, the big loser wishes he could check out early at a pop-up fashion show.

title: Blue Man Dupe
subtitle: Blue Man Dupe
shortDescription: Murr, Joe, Q and Sal are a little too generous with fellow shoppers at the market, then ask strangers to help them out of a texting jam. Plus, the big loser fights his way - repeatedly - to the best seat in the house.

title: The Dumbbell
subtitle: The Dumbbell
shortDescription: Joe, Sal, Q and Murr test their parental instincts by reading their daughters' diaries, then give presentations that are anything but normal. And tonight's big loser gets painfully honest with bodybuilders at the gym.

title: The Eggman
subtitle: The Eggman
shortDescription: Joe, Q, Sal and Murr go incognito to fool unsuspecting strangers, then pop in for a coffee just in time to miss out on a big prize. Plus, tonight's big loser might just crack under the pressure of his rotten punishment.

title: Cake Loss
subtitle: Cake Loss
shortDescription: Q, Sal, Murr and Joe mean no disrespect to patrons at a food court, then cut to the chase while posing as tailors. Later, strangers pick sides in a wild debate, and tonight's big loser takes the cake with his crumby punishment.

title: The Antisocial Network
subtitle: The Antisocial Network
shortDescription: Sal, Murr, Joe and Q play matchmakers at the food court, then switch fields to pose as architects, sharing some perplexing new building technology. Plus, tonight's big loser makes a connection while networking - and won't let go.

title: Off the Reservation
subtitle: Off the Reservation
shortDescription: The guys partake in a fake documentary, and tonight's big loser is the host with the least!

title: Fraudway
subtitle: Fraudway
shortDescription: Q, Joe, Sal and Murr one-up each other while trying not to laugh, then team up for a lunch that's for the birds. Later, tonight's big loser hits the Broadway stage, where he's treated to a classic New York welcome by an agitated crowd.

title: The Show Stopper
subtitle: The Show Stopper
shortDescription: Sal, Q, Joe and Murr are at Universal Studios in Hollywood! They start off serving up ridiculous surveys, then make things awkward while posing as maintenance workers. Tonight's big loser can't catch a break, no matter how hard he tries.

title: Sucks for You
subtitle: Sucks for You
shortDescription: Sal, Q, Joe and Murr bus their way through Katz's Deli, then express some unpopular opinions at the park. Plus, tonight's big loser must talk his way through some real highs and lows, in a punishment that truly sucks.

title: Well...
subtitle: Well...
shortDescription: Q, Sal, Joe and Murr play a game of tag at a coffee shop, then convince shoppers to deliver sketchy messages at the grocery store. Plus, tonight's big loser might lose his mind in Impractical Jokers' first-ever non-punishment punishment!

title: The Prize Fighter
subtitle: The Prize Fighter
shortDescription: Q, Sal, Murr and Joe get their checks bounced by customers who notice unusual charges, then help out coworkers with some peculiar trust exercises. Later, the big loser finds himself balls-deep at a rigged carnival game.

title: Sun-Fan Lotion
subtitle: Sun-Fan Lotion
shortDescription: Joe, Murr, Q and Sal are at the massage parlor for much kneaded relaxation, and then ask strangers their opinions on questionable yearbook ads. Later, tonight's big loser has an awkward but fan-tastic time in the sun.

title: Urine Trouble
subtitle: Urine Trouble
shortDescription: Joe, Sal, Q and Murr play receptionists looking for suspicious names. The guys seek marriage advice from strangers after a private eye shares incriminating photos. The loser goes from pissed off to pissed on in the matter of one punishment.

title: Irritable Vowel Syndrome
subtitle: Irritable Vowel Syndrome

subtitle: Bad Carma
shortDescription: Murr, Sal, Joe and Q showcase questionable products to participants, and then rescue strangers who don't need to be rescued. Later, the big loser must hit and run his mouth to get himself out of trouble.

title: Fast Feud
subtitle: Fast Feud
shortDescription: Four longtime friends compete to embarrass each other with a series of hilarious dares. If they refuse, they lose. At the end, the big loser must endure an epic punishment.

subtitle: Hollywood
shortDescription: The guys fly to LA to try directing, then meet up with Jay and Silent Bob to "pants" the town red.

title: Toll Booth Corrector
subtitle: Toll Booth Corrector
shortDescription: The guys get in a wild debate judged by a stranger and the loser is put in a real tight spot.

title: The Paternity Test
subtitle: The Paternity Test
shortDescription: The guys pose as hotel concierges and try committing insurance fraud with the help of strangers.

title: The Shame of Water
subtitle: The Shame of Water
shortDescription: The guys fight with significant others in public. The loser is on shaky ground while waiting tables.

title: Rock Bottom
subtitle: Rock Bottom
shortDescription: The guys "do the farts" with Jeff Daniels and try to get people to take their sides in an argument.

title: It's Electric
subtitle: It's Electric
shortDescription: The big loser heads to the spa for an electrifying punishment two years in the making.

title: Fantasy Draft
subtitle: Fantasy Draft
shortDescription: Joey Fatone joins forces with NBA star\/IJ superfan Mo Bamba and teammate Terrance Ross. Seated together, the three guys have one goal: to assemble the ultimate professional Impractical Jokers team.

title: Summer Vacation
subtitle: Summer Vacation
shortDescription: Sun's out, fun's out? Tune in to see Joe, Q, Murr and Sal in their very best\/worst vacation challenges and punishments, with some helpful hints along the way.

title: Joker for a Day Part 2
subtitle: Joker for a Day Part 2
shortDescription: Joe, Murr, Q, and Sal take their crew by surprise again for another super-secret episode, sending brand new faces in front of the camera to compete in classic Impractical Jokers challenges.

title: Celebrating 200 Episodes: The First Hundred
subtitle: Celebrating 200 Episodes: The First Hundred
shortDescription: Join Joe, Murr, Q, and Sal as they reminisce about the first hundred episodes of Impractical Jokers!

title: Celebrating 200 Episodes: The Second Hundred
subtitle: Celebrating 200 Episodes: The Second Hundred
shortDescription: Join Joe, Murr, Q, and Sal as they reminisce about the past hundred episodes of Impractical Jokers!

title: Impractical Jokers: Slam Dunks
subtitle: Impractical Jokers: Slam Dunks
shortDescription: NBA stars Richard Jefferson and Channing Frye join Casey Jost to shoot hoops at Joe, Q, Murr and Sal's alma mater, Monsignor Farrell High School, and rate the guys performances of past seasons! Who will be named Jokers slam dunk champion?

title: Adam Ruins Giving
subtitle: Adam Ruins Giving
shortDescription: Tonight, host Adam Conover dispels widespread misconceptions about everything from diamond engagement rings to canned goods.

title: Adam Ruins Security
subtitle: Adam Ruins Security
shortDescription: Adam sets his sights on security theater, explaining that airport security wastes too much of our time and money, medicine safety seals do nothing to protect us, and your credit card number isn't remotely secure.

title: Adam Ruins Cars
subtitle: Adam Ruins Cars
shortDescription: Adam dives into the much-beloved auto industry and exposes the surprising truths behind car dealerships, car ownership and the concept of "jaywalking."

title: Adam Ruins Forensic Science
subtitle: Adam Ruins Forensic Science
shortDescription: Adam Ruins Forensic Science: Adam uncovers the scary truth behind unreliable methods used to build evidence in criminal cases - which often send innocent people to jail.

title: Adam Ruins Restaurants
subtitle: Adam Ruins Restaurants
shortDescription: Adam dives deep into the hidden truths of dining out. He explains why tipping we'd be better off without, experts can't tell the difference between wines, and reveals fraudulently labeled seafood is rampant.

title: Adam Ruins Hygiene
subtitle: Adam Ruins Hygiene
shortDescription: Adam reveals that the term halitosis was popularized in a 1920s ad campaign that used cruel ads to make people insecure about their breath, and explains why running water is one of the greatest miracles of the modern age.

title: Adam Ruins Voting
subtitle: Adam Ruins Voting
shortDescription: Adam explores the twisted history of the Electoral College, explaining that the Founding Fathers did not want most Americans to vote. He also takes a stab at fixing a political system that seems rigged against True democracy.

title: Adam Ruins Work
shortDescription: Adam shows how the 40-hour work week not only exhausts employees but also arms businesses, reveals the legal mess of hiring interns and freelancers, and explores how discussing your salary with co-workers is actually a good thing.
description: Adam shows how the 40-hour work week not only exhausts employees but also arms businesses, reveals the legal mess of hiring interns and freelancers, and explores how discussing your salary with co-workers is actually a good thing.

descriptionNoTags: Adam shows how the 40-hour work week not only exhausts employees but also arms businesses, reveals the legal mess of hiring interns and freelancers, and explores how discussing your salary with co-workers is actually a good thing.

title: Adam Ruins Summer Fun
subtitle: Adam Ruins Summer Fun
shortDescription: Adam crashes the last day of summer by revealing extended vacations makes you dumber, and Mickey Mouse has made a mess of our copyright laws. Adam also unveils a surprising gender bias in the world of videogames.

title: Adam Ruins Sex
subtitle: Adam Ruins Sex
shortDescription: Adam reveals that circumcision was popularized by a bunch of masturbation-curbing 19th century prudes. Plus, he reveals why the fear of having herpes is overblown and explores why the term "pop your cherry" is a bunch of nonsense.

title: Adam Ruins Nutrition
subtitle: Adam Ruins Nutrition
shortDescription: Adam shows why vitamin supplements don't make us any healthier, and that the "balanced breakfast" we've been sold is anything but. Later, he reveals how most of the nutritional science the media reports on isn't science at all.

title: Adam Ruins Death
subtitle: Adam Ruins Death
shortDescription: Adam explains the end is inevitable, shows why immortality is a fantasy and reveals that the American funeral industry is a racket that exploits mourners' grief and fear of dying.

title: Adam Ruins Hollywood
subtitle: Adam Ruins Hollywood
shortDescription: Straight from the red carpet, with help from celebrity guests Rachel Bloom and Ariana Madix, Adam exposes the hidden truths behind Hollywood's glitz and glamour, from the clothes stars wear to the process behind movie ratings.

title: Adam Ruins Football
subtitle: Adam Ruins Football
shortDescription: Adam hits the gridiron to explain why the playoffs rarely determine which team is best, and then explores how hydration myths spread by sports drink companies put kids at risk. Adam also tackles football-caused brain injuries.

title: Adam Ruins Weddings
subtitle: Adam Ruins Weddings
shortDescription: Emily and Murph's wedding day is here but Adam's gift of information may rain on their parade. Adam reveals how most wedding traditions were recently created by consumerism, and divorce is actually a wonderful thing.

title: Adam Ruins Shopping Malls
subtitle: Adam Ruins Shopping Malls
shortDescription: Adam and Emily go on a shopping spree of knowledge and find that malls were created as tax loopholes, nutrient supplements are often unregulated, and most eyeglasses are made by one manufacturer that inflates its prices.

title: Adam Ruins Animals
subtitle: Adam Ruins Animals
shortDescription: Adam explores how purebred dogs are genetic monsters created by bored Victorians, domestic cats are overpopulated killing machines that threaten other animals and wild animal trophy hunting can actually help endangered species.

title: Adam Ruins Immigration
subtitle: Adam Ruins Immigration
shortDescription: Adam illustrates how a border wall wouldn't keep out legal immigrants who overstay their visas, racist mass deportations have historically led to disaster, and immigration courts are a huge mess.

title: Adam Ruins Housing
subtitle: Adam Ruins Housing
shortDescription: Adam gets evicted from his home, and while searching for a new place, he exposes the harsh realities of real estate. Plus, Adam explains why helping the homeless is a lot simpler and more straightforward than you might think.

title: Adam Ruins Drugs
subtitle: Adam Ruins Drugs
shortDescription: Adam weeds through the misconceptions of marijuana and exposes the blunt truth about the War on Drugs. It stemmed from a racist and political agenda. Plus, Adam illustrates why prescription pills are the True gateway drug.

title: Adam Ruins Prison
subtitle: Adam Ruins Prison
shortDescription: When Emily gets tossed in the slammer, her cellmate reveals corporations make money off prison inmates while the system does nothing to reduce crime. Adam then sheds light on jail rehabilitation and solitary confinement.

title: Adam Ruins the Wild West
subtitle: Adam Ruins the Wild West
shortDescription: Adam reveals how prostitution, despite its reputation, actually helped settle the West. He then explains why the All-American Cowboy is a myth and the real western hero wasn't a person. It was air conditioning.

title: Adam Ruins Justice
subtitle: Adam Ruins Justice
shortDescription: After getting Emily out of prison, Adam and his sister Rhea take on the Justice system, showing that juries simply can't be impartial and the prosecution team is way better and well funded than your court appointed lawyer.

title: Adam Ruins Christmas
subtitle: Adam Ruins Christmas
shortDescription: Ho ho huh?! Adam teaches his sister that the real St. Nick story is a lot creepier than she thought, and modern Santa was created by commercialism only a century ago. Adam also reveals how gift-giving actually hurts the economy.

title: Adam Ruins Going Green
subtitle: Adam Ruins Going Green
shortDescription: Adam meets a young dad on a personal mission to save the world and end climate change until Adam turns his world upside down. Find out why electric cars and green products don't make the impact you've been promised.

title: Adam Ruins Having a Baby
subtitle: Adam Ruins Having a Baby
shortDescription: Adam dispels the myth about getting pregnant after 35, delves into breastfeeding vs formula, and explores postpartum depression for women - and men.

title: Adam Ruins Weight Loss
subtitle: Adam Ruins Weight Loss
shortDescription: Host Adam Conover illustrates all the reasons low-fat diets can actually make you fatter, and why counting calories is a waste of time.

title: Adam Ruins the Hospital
subtitle: Adam Ruins the Hospital
shortDescription: Adam Conover explains that inflated hospital costs have created a system that's unaffordable and unfair. Plus, the reckless prescription of antibiotics is making them worthless, and you might not need a mammogram.

title: Adam Ruins Dating
subtitle: Adam Ruins Dating
shortDescription: Adam swipes right on knowledge by exposing the flaws in dating sites. Plus, alpha males (and wolves) don't exist, and personality tests are a failure.

title: Adam Ruins Art
subtitle: Adam Ruins Art
shortDescription: Adam shows why popular art is revered, regardless of merit. He also exposes the masters as copycats and reveals the art market to be a moneymaking scheme.

title: Adam Ruins What We Learned in School
subtitle: Adam Ruins What We Learned in School
shortDescription: In his first animated episode, Adam teaches a crew of kids and their teacher that Christopher Columbus didn't discover America, King Tut was a dud, and the rules of grammar are not as ironclad as you'd think.

title: Adam Ruins College
subtitle: Adam Ruins College
shortDescription: Adam explains why the odds of becoming a dropout billionaire are not in your favor, how manipulated school rankings have little to do with education quality and why the privatization of student loans created a massive debt crisis.

title: Emily Ruins Adam
subtitle: Emily Ruins Adam
shortDescription: Emily takes over to "ruin" Adam, pointing out where his facts fall short. She debunks the idea that IQ tests measure intelligence and points to information Adam has gotten wrong in the past. Plus, she explains the "backfire effect."

title: Adam Ruins His Vacation
subtitle: Adam Ruins His Vacation
shortDescription: Get ready for some R&R (Ruining and more Ruining!), as Adam Conover and his girlfriend take a journey across America.

title: Adam Ruins the Suburbs
subtitle: Adam Ruins the Suburbs
shortDescription: Adam explains that your lawn is an unnatural monstrosity, suburban design is killing you, and the racist past of suburbs led to segregation in schools.

title: Adam Ruins The Economy
subtitle: Adam Ruins The Economy
shortDescription: Adam explains why doing taxes is unnecessarily complicated, the economic numbers we hear don't reveal much, and American manufacturing can't return.

title: Adam Ruins Conspiracy Theories
subtitle: Adam Ruins Conspiracy Theories
shortDescription: Adam Conover debunks the fake moon landing theory, discusses the Satanic Panic of the 1980s and reveals how to spot a False theory.

title: Adam Ruins Spa Day
subtitle: Adam Ruins Spa Day
shortDescription: Pricey detox treatments may do more harm than good, MSG's scary reputation is undeserved, and the placebo effect is way more powerful than you think!

title: Adam Ruins Halloween
subtitle: Adam Ruins Halloween
shortDescription: Strangers with poisoned candy don't exist, the panic over Orson Welles' War of the Worlds broadcast didn't happen and mediums are total frauds.

title: Adam Ruins Science
subtitle: Adam Ruins Science
shortDescription: Testing on mice is a waste, and scarce funding stops scientists from seeking cures and proving their findings.

title: Adam Ruins the Future
subtitle: Adam Ruins the Future
shortDescription: Unregulated food expiration dates lead to massive waste, your 401(k) won't be enough to support your retirement and the future is unpredictable.

title: Give Me Liberty or Give Me Truth
subtitle: Give Me Liberty or Give Me Truth
shortDescription: Reanimated History: Adam Conover undermines everything you thought you knew about the American Revolution.

title: The First Factsgiving
subtitle: The First Factsgiving
shortDescription: Reanimated History: The Pilgrims were grave robbers, Pocahontas and John Smith's romance never happened, and huge cities in the New World existed before its "discovery."

title: Mutually Assured Ruination
subtitle: Mutually Assured Ruination
shortDescription: Reanimated History: The Cuban Missile Crisis was started by the US, a female politician stood up to McCarthy, and a mistake actually brought down the Berlin Wall.

title: An Ancient History of Violence
subtitle: An Ancient History of Violence
shortDescription: Reanimated History: Gladiators were barred from killing opponents, one Celtic woman nearly brought down the Romans, and the brave "300" Spartans were really 7000.

title: The Copernican Ruin-aissance
subtitle: The Copernican Ruin-aissance
shortDescription: Reanimated History: Adam sheds some light on Copernicus, a rogue dwarf revolutionized what we know about the human body, and wait until you hear about Tulip Mania!

title: 100 Years Ago Today
subtitle: 100 Years Ago Today
shortDescription: Reanimated History: Adam digs into the Panama Canal, death by food, and the even deadlier Spanish Flu.

title: Adam Ruins Guns
subtitle: Adam Ruins Guns
shortDescription: Adam Conover is back to take aim at critics on both sides of the gun debate in America. He explains why an assault weapons ban would not be effective and demonstrates how the Second Amendment has been twisted to fit the NRA's agenda.

title: Adam Ruins Sleep
subtitle: Adam Ruins Sleep
shortDescription: Adam Conover has a rude awakening for everything you thought you knew about sleep (or lack of it), from the mattress industry to supposedly lazy teens to sleep aids.

title: Adam Ruins Tech
subtitle: Adam Ruins Tech
shortDescription: Adam Conover downloads you on how the tech industry isn't really as helpful as you think - or wants you to think.

title: Adam Ruins Flying
subtitle: Adam Ruins Flying
shortDescription: Adam causes turbulence when he reveals that reward miles drive up costs, and revisits the "golden age" of air travel to uncover smoky, sexist death traps in the sky. Plus, airline mergers are crippling smaller cities.

title: Adam Ruins a Plate of Nachos
subtitle: Adam Ruins a Plate of Nachos
shortDescription: Adam dishes out the facts on the avocado trade being ruled by drug cartels, and Big Pork making bacon a pop culture hit while covering up its huge health risks. Plus, America's food problems stem from corn.

title: Adam Ruins a Sitcom
subtitle: Adam Ruins a Sitcom
shortDescription: Adam tackles classic television stereotypes, from the racism behind public pools, to the "model minority" myth of Asian Americans, to the on-screen toxic masculinity that's masking the problems young men face today.

title: Adam Ruins Games
subtitle: Adam Ruins Games
shortDescription: Adam hits pause on the myth that connects video games to real-life violence, and reveals that Monopoly was a rip-off of an anti-capitalist teaching game. Plus, Olympic organizers get rich while athletes struggle to get by.

title: Adam Ruins Nature
subtitle: Adam Ruins Nature
shortDescription: Adam digs up the dirt on nature, revealing that Mount Everest is a frozen pile of poop, natural disasters are actually man-made, and there is no such thing as untouched wilderness.

title: Adam Ruins America
subtitle: Adam Ruins America
shortDescription: Adam lets his freedom flag fly by examining why America doesn't have higher rates of social mobility. He then uncovers the flaws within our constitution and examines our country's progression and regression.

title: Adam Ruins a Night Out
subtitle: Adam Ruins a Night Out
shortDescription: Adam and Emily prepare for a big night out by revealing the marketing ploy that led to women shaving and the fashion agendas that created pockets. Then, the two friends pour back the truth on alcohol consumption.

title: Adam Ruins Doing Good
subtitle: Adam Ruins Doing Good
shortDescription: Adam takes down the do-gooders and reveals how Teach For America is harmful to both students and teachers. He then uncovers the ineffectiveness of recycling and calls out the billionaires who create charities for tax breaks.

title: Adam Ruins a Murder
subtitle: Adam Ruins a Murder
shortDescription: Adam shines a headlight on why drivers are rarely prosecuted for car accidents that result in death. He breaks down border patrol's problematic search policies and examines the messed-up history of corpses and medical studies.

title: Adam Ruins Music
subtitle: Adam Ruins Music
shortDescription: It's time to face the music, as Adam reveals the racism behind rock & roll's origins and the egregious fees of Live Nation's monopoly. He then defends musicians who "sell out" to make a living in today's digital landscape.

title: Adam Ruins Little Bugs
subtitle: Adam Ruins Little Bugs
shortDescription: Don't let Adam's facts bug you as he uncovers the benefits of spiders, serves up knowledge on why we should be eating more bugs as a protein source, and illustrates the benefits of little bugs on your gut health.

title: Adam Ruins Cops
subtitle: Adam Ruins Cops
shortDescription: Adam polices the truth behind the overuse of SWAT Teams, illustrates how using school officers can create a pipeline for prisons, and examines the origins and intended purpose of police officers.

title: Adam Ruins Himself
subtitle: Adam Ruins Himself
shortDescription: In the season finale, Adam battles with his inner self-doubt over how biases affect the show. He then exposes the shortcomings of story-telling, and the influence (or lack thereof) of advertising on the series' integrity.

subtitle: Milk and Cookies

subtitle: Rare Air

subtitle: Canadian Tuxedo

subtitle: Balls Get in the Way

subtitle: I'm Cool

subtitle: Borderline Relatable
shortDescription: Comedian\/actor Aasif Mandvi talks about his vices, actor John Ross Bowie is an open book about Heathers he's dated, and comedian Phoebe Robinson "Chers" a boob grazing story. Plus, not one, but two special surprise guests!

subtitle: Those Damn Housewives
shortDescription: Actress Wendi McLendon Covey dishes on the drama in the LBC, comedian Jonah Ray bums cash from the crowd and funny lady Michelle Buteau tells of her indecent proposal. But only one can be named best talk show guest in America.

subtitle: Wig Toss

subtitle: Ankle Cleavage

subtitle: Hot Gossip

subtitle: Melissa Joan Hart, Caroline Rhea, Jared Logan
shortDescription: Actresses Melissa Joan Hart and Caroline Rhea have a mini-Sabrina the Teenage Witch reunion, and Jared Logan beats up jocks. Plus, find out who will win the title of "Best Talk Show Guest in America!"

shortDescription: Colin Quinn and Charles Barkley trash-talk their way through the competition, but are they a match for Broadway diva Marissa Jaret Winokur? Plus, find out who's "Best Talk Show Guest in America!"

subtitle: Fortune Feimster, Reggie Bush, and Nick Thune

subtitle: Cheryl Hines, Ron Funches, Michael Kosta
shortDescription: Actress Cheryl Hines channels Larry David while double-fisting drinks, comedian Ron Funches shows his mischievous spirit and The Daily Show's Michael Kosta brings a very special guest as his secret weapon.

subtitle: Billy Eichner, David Koechner, Lauren Lapkus
shortDescription: All bets are off tonight, as David Koechner's disorderly style clashes with the judges. But will his disruptive play distract fellow competitors Lauren Lapkus and Billy Eichner? Watch to find out!

subtitle: Cooking for One

subtitle: Gift Giving

subtitle: Entertaining for Peanuts

subtitle: Holidays

title: Out of This World
subtitle: Out of This World

subtitle: Making Love

subtitle: Murdercide

subtitle: Teenagers

subtitle: Creativity

subtitle: All About Amy

subtitle: Makeover

subtitle: Anniversary

subtitle: Halloween

subtitle: Game Night

shortDescription: The guys get a taste of babysitting while asking reluctant strangers to watch their kid, then head to the grocery store to conduct taste(less) tests with shoppers, and the loser is forced to strip for the wrong people.

title: The Taunted House
subtitle: The Taunted House
shortDescription: The guys get extra cheesy at a pizza parlor, then head to Wall Street where they ask strangers to help translate bizarre text messages in Spanish. And trapped in a haunted house, a nightmare comes to life for tonight's big loser.

title: Doomed
subtitle: Doomed

title: HellCopter
subtitle: HellCopter

subtitle: You're Cut Off

subtitle: Ruffled Feathers

subtitle: Stare Master

title: Bidder Loser
subtitle: Bidder Loser

title: The Good, the Bad and the Punished
subtitle: The Good, the Bad and the Punished

title: Putting the P in Pool
subtitle: Putting the P in Pool
shortDescription: The guys pose as crummy cashiers at a grocery store and then head to the mall for a touching game involving laser pointers. Plus, the loser is soaked with embarrassment after making it clear to some swimmers that he's #1.

subtitle: Statue of Limitations

subtitle: Brother of the Sisterhood

subtitle: Dark Side of the Moon

subtitle: Whose Phone Is Ringing?

subtitle: Centaur of Attention

subtitle: Browbeaten

subtitle: The Coward

subtitle: Virtual Insanity

title: Laundry Day
subtitle: Laundry Day

subtitle: Water Torture

subtitle: Hitting the Wrong Note

subtitle: Heckle and Hide

subtitle: The Chairman

subtitle: Wrapper's Delight

subtitle: Ash Clown

subtitle: Spider Man

subtitle: Stage Fright

subtitle: Training Day

subtitle: The Parent Trap

subtitle: Medium, Well Done

subtitle: Turning the Tables

subtitle: The Running of the Bullies

subtitle: Chick Magnet

subtitle: Dropping Knowledge

subtitle: Hump Day

subtitle: Out of Left Field

subtitle: Autograph Corrector

subtitle: The Bogey Man

subtitle: Hell on Wheels

subtitle: The Jokers Games

subtitle: Spring Break Countdown

subtitle: The Dumbbell
shortDescription: Joe, Sal, Q and Murr test their parental instincts by reading their daughters' diaries, then give presentations that are anything but normal. And tonight's big loser gets painfully honest with bodybuilders at the gym.

subtitle: The Eggman

subtitle: The Antisocial Network

subtitle: Off the Reservation

subtitle: Sucks for You

subtitle: The Prize Fighter

subtitle: Irritable Vowel Syndrome

shortDescription: Murr, Sal, Joe and Q showcase questionable products to participants, and then rescue strangers who don't need to be rescued. Later, the big loser must hit and run his mouth to get himself out of trouble.

subtitle: Toll Booth Corrector
shortDescription: The guys get in a wild debate judged by a stranger and the loser is put in a real tight spot.

subtitle: The Paternity Test

title: The Shame of Water
subtitle: The Shame of Water

subtitle: Rock Bottom
shortDescription: The guys "do the farts" with Jeff Daniels and try to get people to take their sides in an argument.

subtitle: It's Electric

subtitle: Summer Vacation

subtitle: Celebrating 200 Episodes: The First Hundred

subtitle: Celebrating 200 Episodes: The Second Hundred
shortDescription: Join Joe, Murr, Q, and Sal as they reminisce about the past hundred episodes of Impractical Jokers!

title: Impractical Jokers: Slam Dunks
subtitle: Impractical Jokers: Slam Dunks

title: Camping
subtitle: Camping
