title: Cycling
subtitle: Cycling
shortDescription: Comedian Jon Glaser takes on cycling for the next episode of his gear show, but gets sidetracked when his e-sidekick, Gear-i, writes an epic script about a post-apocalyptic bike messenger. Michael Shannon and Janeane Garofalo guest star.

title: Hockey
subtitle: Hockey
shortDescription: Jon Glaser loves hockey. But the fact that he never learned to skate until he was an adult sends him on a collision course of emotions involving his mommy and his son. Former NHL great Ron Duguay guest stars.

title: Dogs
subtitle: Dogs
shortDescription: Man's best friend deserves the best gear. But when Jon's gear show is interrupted by a neighborhood dog owner who doesn't clean up his pup's poop, Jon comes up with a plan to exact his revenge.

title: Fishing
subtitle: Fishing
shortDescription: Jon hasn't fished much - however, he's very excited to enjoy all the sweet gear. But a relaxing fishing excursion soon turns into a crushing torrent of anxiety that leaves Jon's psyche battered. Pro bass fisherman Woo Daves guest stars.

title: Baseball
subtitle: Baseball

subtitle: Surfing

subtitle: Space
shortDescription: Jon takes one giant leap for gearkind as he prepares to head to space! That is, until Jon's last meal on earth thrusts him into a psychological battle with a cold-blooded killer. MMA legend, Renzo Gracie guest stars.

title: Leisure
shortDescription: With his real family away, Jon decides to film in his real home and kick back in the "chill zone" with his bros. But when they all bail, Jon is left scrambling to salvage his weekend. Will gear save Jon from two days of loneliness?

subtitle: Sailing

subtitle: Survival

subtitle: Tennis

title: Football
subtitle: Football
shortDescription: Jon gears up for his son's first football game with a kick-ass tailgate. But when the mysterious art of magic gets in the way, Jon must confront a deep secret from his past. New York Jets superfan Fireman Ed and Christine Taylor guest star.

title: Golf
subtitle: Golf
shortDescription: Golf turns philosophical when a ghost from gear past forces Jon to make a difficult choice; a choice that could threaten to put a permanent wedge between Jon, his trusted 'Spurt, and the network.

title: Basketball
subtitle: Basketball
shortDescription: Jon's vasectomy isn't going to stop him from shooting a super cool episode about basketball. But when his prolonged recovery starts crossing lines, he risks a mutiny among his cast and crew, including his trusted 'Spurt.

title: Road Trip
subtitle: Road Trip
shortDescription: Jon and his real family hit the road for a snowboarding vacation and all the cool gear that comes with it. But things quickly turn ominous when Jon realizes his son may be the Anti-Gear!

title: Photography
subtitle: Photography

subtitle: Swing Dancing

subtitle: Gearing

title: The Marathon Man
subtitle: The Marathon Man
shortDescription: Sal, Murr, Q and Joe climb to the Top of the Rock for some awkward interactions, then "wet" appetites at a bagel shop. And the big loser suits up - or down - for a run across the Brooklyn Bridge that's anything but inspiring.

title: Guilty as Charged
subtitle: Guilty as Charged
shortDescription: Murr, Sal, Joe and Q enlist shoppers to help them avoid a security guard out to get them, and the guys get spacey while teaching about UFOs. Plus, the big loser faces the wrath of a crowd of rockers who are ready to rumble.

title: No Good Deed
subtitle: No Good Deed
shortDescription: Q, Sal, Murr and Joe compete in a focus group face-off, convincing people that their TV show ideas are the tops, and tonight's losers might get run out of town when they reveal their financial mismanagement plan to charity donors.

title: Stripteased
subtitle: Stripteased
shortDescription: Murr, Joe, Q and Sal return to the dentist's office, then try to make each other laugh in a food court tournament. And the big loser strips for a rowdy group of ladies who will never be able to un-see the sorry state of his skin.

title: Indecent Proposal
subtitle: Indecent Proposal
shortDescription: Sal, Murr, Joe and Q don absurd disguises to trick unsuspecting receptionists, then try to convince strangers to sign off on some unusual emails. Plus, the big loser turns a harmless dance class into a dance with danger.

title: Turning the Tables
subtitle: Turning the Tables
shortDescription: Sal, Joe, Murr and Q take a spin in a motorized chair hoping the kindness of strangers will keep them on track, and tonight's big loser walks away bruised and battered when he's forced to clear some tables in an unusual way.

title: Lords of the Ring
subtitle: Lords of the Ring
shortDescription: Joe, Murr, Sal and Q skirt the law while posing as receptionists, then go fishing at an unlikely locale. And the heat is on tonight's big losers as they try to give one unlucky customer the deal of a lifetime.

title: No Child Left Behind
subtitle: No Child Left Behind
shortDescription: Q, Murr, Joe and Sal pitch toys that should be kept away from tots, face off at a market (resulting in some pinched nerves), and see spots at the mall. Plus, the big loser sticks his nose where it doesn't belong.

title: Pulling the Rug
subtitle: Pulling the Rug
shortDescription: Joe, Murr, Q and Sal run a surprise challenge, and a stint at The Cake Boss's counter is anything but sweet. Then, advice for kids turns awkward when heard by strangers, and tonight's loser looks for a new 'do - but not for himself.

title: Speech Impediment
subtitle: Speech Impediment
shortDescription: Joe, Q, Sal and Murr crack each other up while performing strange scenes behind glass, then test out awkward proposals at the Top of the Rock. And the big loser gets tongue-tied while speaking before government officials.

title: Card Against Humanity
subtitle: Card Against Humanity
shortDescription: Q, Murr, Joe and Sal have customers seeing red while working at an optician's office, then get too close for comfort eavesdropping on strangers' conversations. Plus, the big loser gives the business at a networking event.

title: Bull Shiatsu
subtitle: Bull Shiatsu
shortDescription: Sal, Joe, Murr and Q try to hold it together as receptionists checking in some strange characters. Later, they offer up odd rewards to helpful strangers, and the big loser gets the stuffing squished out of him at the mall.

title: The Running of the Bullies
subtitle: The Running of the Bullies
shortDescription: Q, Murr, Joe and Sal offer up peculiar specials at a steakhouse and get creepy while helping to clean a prop house. Plus, tonight's big loser realizes he may need his own lifeguard after making waves at the pool.

title: The Needy and the Greedy
subtitle: The Needy and the Greedy
shortDescription: Joe, Murr, Q and Sal have fast fingers at a focus group and leave no cereal box unturned at the grocery store. Then, tonight's big loser opens a can of something fierce at a local donation center.

title: Washed Up
subtitle: Washed Up
shortDescription: Q, Joe, Sal and Murr rat each other out at a pizza place and get into textual relationships with strangers at the mall. Then, the big loser twerks hard for the money at an impromptu bikini car wash.

title: To Hatch a Predator
subtitle: To Hatch a Predator
shortDescription: The Jokers perform unusual methods of DNA testing and get too close for comfort at the grocery store. Then, tonight's big loser becomes a shell of a man after he cracks under pressure during a presentation at a children's museum.

title: Like a Boss
subtitle: Like a Boss
shortDescription: The Jokers act fast and furiously as employees at a theme park and go postal on model citizens who don't realize they're part of the picture. Then, tonight's big loser tumbles and falls after antagonizing a room full of Guy Fieri fans.

title: Chick Magnet
subtitle: Chick Magnet
shortDescription: The guys turn on the charm to make a restaurant basement sound enticing and recruit unsuspecting shoppers to shout out bizarre nicknames. Then, tonight's big loser must find his way out of the cuckoo's nest before the chicks get crazy!

title: Dropping Knowledge
subtitle: Dropping Knowledge
shortDescription: The guys pump the breaks on a bike ride to ask perplexed strangers for help and cut the java line to get the go-ahead on some very strange emails. Plus tonight's big loser gets schooled in a game show that barely makes the grade.

title: Hump Day
subtitle: Hump Day
shortDescription: Q, Sal, Joe and Murr Greek out while lending a hand to customers at a casual restaurant, then battle across the table of a focus group. Plus the big loser gets spitting mad when forced to spend some quality time at the zoo.

title: Out of Left Field
subtitle: Out of Left Field
shortDescription: The guys try not to crack up during a four-way face off and later find that a stroll with the Gatto pups is no walk in the park. Plus, tonight's big loser suffers more than muscle failure in a major league embarrassment.

title: Autograph Corrector
subtitle: Autograph Corrector
shortDescription: The guys rely on the kindness of strangers to help answer some awkward questions, then go looking for love in the park. Plus, tonight's big loser strikes out amongst baseball fans with an assist from Yankees legend Tino Martinez.

title: The Bogey Man
subtitle: The Bogey Man
shortDescription: The laughing gas flows freely when the guys pose as dental assistants. Later they make headlines for all the wrong reasons and get burned giving some campfire tips. Plus the big loser scores a hole in none on the links.

title: Hell on Wheels
subtitle: Hell on Wheels
shortDescription: The guys try and work out the kinks as physical therapists, then pitch some way out-of-the-box ideas for TV hosts. Plus, the big loser gets rolled over by some speedy ladies.

title: Pantsing with the Stars
subtitle: Pantsing with the Stars
shortDescription: The guys pair up to share educational ideas with perplexed parents, then teach Krav Maga to martial arts newbies. But when one Joker refuses, he becomes the big loser and faces an opponent that scares the pants off him.

title: Staten Island Holiday Spectacular
subtitle: Staten Island Holiday Spectacular
shortDescription: The guys celebrate with some unseasonable specials, followed by new toys you may not want under the tree. Then, gift wrapping goes awry, and the big loser has a close encounter with some hungry wild life.

title: The Jokers Games
subtitle: The Jokers Games
shortDescription: Get ready to judge Joe, Murr, Sal and Q on the exemplary skills (or lack thereof) that they've displayed over the years. Host Joey Fatone is joined by championship athletes, and past punishers, to see how the guys measure up.

title: March Madness Breakdown
subtitle: March Madness Breakdown
shortDescription: Tune in to find out which Joker is this year's top draft pick as determined by NBA stars Doug McDermott and Enes Kanter, along with host Joey Fatone - not an NBA star.

title: Spring Break Countdown
subtitle: Spring Break Countdown
shortDescription: Make a splash as we count down Q, Murr, Sal and Joe's most cringeworthy, embarrassing and hilarious moments of fun in the sun. Plus, you'll come away with a dozen totally ridiculous spring break tips to take with you!

title: Joker for a Day
subtitle: Joker for a Day
shortDescription: Joe, Sal, Murr, and Q surprise their crew by flipping the cameras on them in this special episode. Watch as members of the Jokers family emerge from behind the scenes to compete in classic games as their bosses egg them on.

title: Hits, Errors & Balls!
subtitle: Hits, Errors & Balls!
shortDescription: Join the guys as they count down the top 9 greatest baseball moments in Impractical Jokers history! Find out who used to be an athlete and who is often stopped by stadium security. Plus, never-before-seen bonus footage!

title: Holiday Party
subtitle: Holiday Party
shortDescription: Joe, Sal, Q and Murr invite you inside their festive shindig, alongside their beloved crew. It's one event you won't want to miss, chock-full of bonus footage, behind-the-scenes banter, and special gifts - for Sal, anyway. Plus, ham!

title: Crash Test Dummies
subtitle: Crash Test Dummies
shortDescription: Murr, Sal, Joe and Q take some customers for a wild ride, and things get messy when they ask fellow shoppers for a hand. Plus, the big losers suffer a monster punishment that leaves them crushed.

title: The Closer
subtitle: The Closer
shortDescription: Q, Joe, Sal and Murr get tech help from some confused tutors, then play Hot Potato in a shoe store. Plus, the big loser wishes he could press escape during a brutal coffee shop punishment.

title: Tipping Point
subtitle: Tipping Point
shortDescription: Sal, Murr, Joe and Q pull desk duty, and then do strangers a solid by barring them from the bathroom. Plus, the big loser learns the hard way that gratuity is not included.

title: Full Mental Jacket
subtitle: Full Mental Jacket
shortDescription: Joe, Murr, Q and Sal send blood pressure rates sky-high while posing as nurses, then stroll through the store with their wives. Plus, the big loser wishes he could check out early at a pop-up fashion show.

title: Blue Man Dupe
subtitle: Blue Man Dupe
shortDescription: Murr, Joe, Q and Sal are a little too generous with fellow shoppers at the market, then ask strangers to help them out of a texting jam. Plus, the big loser fights his way - repeatedly - to the best seat in the house.

title: The Dumbbell
subtitle: The Dumbbell
shortDescription: Joe, Sal, Q and Murr test their parental instincts by reading their daughters' diaries, then give presentations that are anything but normal. And tonight's big loser gets painfully honest with bodybuilders at the gym.

title: The Eggman
subtitle: The Eggman
shortDescription: Joe, Q, Sal and Murr go incognito to fool unsuspecting strangers, then pop in for a coffee just in time to miss out on a big prize. Plus, tonight's big loser might just crack under the pressure of his rotten punishment.

title: Cake Loss
subtitle: Cake Loss
shortDescription: Q, Sal, Murr and Joe mean no disrespect to patrons at a food court, then cut to the chase while posing as tailors. Later, strangers pick sides in a wild debate, and tonight's big loser takes the cake with his crumby punishment.

title: The Antisocial Network
subtitle: The Antisocial Network
shortDescription: Sal, Murr, Joe and Q play matchmakers at the food court, then switch fields to pose as architects, sharing some perplexing new building technology. Plus, tonight's big loser makes a connection while networking - and won't let go.

title: Off the Reservation
subtitle: Off the Reservation
shortDescription: The guys partake in a fake documentary, and tonight's big loser is the host with the least!

title: Fraudway
subtitle: Fraudway
shortDescription: Q, Joe, Sal and Murr one-up each other while trying not to laugh, then team up for a lunch that's for the birds. Later, tonight's big loser hits the Broadway stage, where he's treated to a classic New York welcome by an agitated crowd.

title: The Show Stopper
subtitle: The Show Stopper
shortDescription: Sal, Q, Joe and Murr are at Universal Studios in Hollywood! They start off serving up ridiculous surveys, then make things awkward while posing as maintenance workers. Tonight's big loser can't catch a break, no matter how hard he tries.

title: Sucks for You
subtitle: Sucks for You
shortDescription: Sal, Q, Joe and Murr bus their way through Katz's Deli, then express some unpopular opinions at the park. Plus, tonight's big loser must talk his way through some real highs and lows, in a punishment that truly sucks.

title: Well...
subtitle: Well...
shortDescription: Q, Sal, Joe and Murr play a game of tag at a coffee shop, then convince shoppers to deliver sketchy messages at the grocery store. Plus, tonight's big loser might lose his mind in Impractical Jokers' first-ever non-punishment punishment!

title: The Prize Fighter
subtitle: The Prize Fighter
shortDescription: Q, Sal, Murr and Joe get their checks bounced by customers who notice unusual charges, then help out coworkers with some peculiar trust exercises. Later, the big loser finds himself balls-deep at a rigged carnival game.

title: Sun-Fan Lotion
subtitle: Sun-Fan Lotion
shortDescription: Joe, Murr, Q and Sal are at the massage parlor for much kneaded relaxation, and then ask strangers their opinions on questionable yearbook ads. Later, tonight's big loser has an awkward but fan-tastic time in the sun.

title: Urine Trouble
subtitle: Urine Trouble
shortDescription: Joe, Sal, Q and Murr play receptionists looking for suspicious names. The guys seek marriage advice from strangers after a private eye shares incriminating photos. The loser goes from pissed off to pissed on in the matter of one punishment.

title: Irritable Vowel Syndrome
subtitle: Irritable Vowel Syndrome
shortDescription: Q, Murr, Sal and Joe seek help from customers when escaping security at the grocery store, then tell bizarre tales to diners at a food court. Plus, the big loser is in consonant hell when he's left looking for a missing letter.

title: Bad Carma
subtitle: Bad Carma
shortDescription: Murr, Sal, Joe and Q showcase questionable products to participants, and then rescue strangers who don't need to be rescued. Later, the big loser must hit and run his mouth to get himself out of trouble.

title: Fast Feud
subtitle: Fast Feud
shortDescription: Four longtime friends compete to embarrass each other with a series of hilarious dares. If they refuse, they lose. At the end, the big loser must endure an epic punishment.

title: Hollywood
subtitle: Hollywood
shortDescription: The guys fly to LA to try directing, then meet up with Jay and Silent Bob to "pants" the town red.

title: Toll Booth Corrector
subtitle: Toll Booth Corrector
shortDescription: The guys get in a wild debate judged by a stranger and the loser is put in a real tight spot.

title: The Paternity Test
subtitle: The Paternity Test
shortDescription: The guys pose as hotel concierges and try committing insurance fraud with the help of strangers.

title: The Shame of Water
subtitle: The Shame of Water
shortDescription: The guys fight with significant others in public. The loser is on shaky ground while waiting tables.

title: Rock Bottom
subtitle: Rock Bottom
shortDescription: The guys "do the farts" with Jeff Daniels and try to get people to take their sides in an argument.

title: It's Electric
subtitle: It's Electric
shortDescription: The big loser heads to the spa for an electrifying punishment two years in the making.

title: Fantasy Draft
subtitle: Fantasy Draft
shortDescription: Joey Fatone joins forces with NBA star\/IJ superfan Mo Bamba and teammate Terrance Ross. Seated together, the three guys have one goal: to assemble the ultimate professional Impractical Jokers team.

title: Summer Vacation
subtitle: Summer Vacation
shortDescription: Sun's out, fun's out? Tune in to see Joe, Q, Murr and Sal in their very best\/worst vacation challenges and punishments, with some helpful hints along the way.

title: Joker for a Day Part 2
subtitle: Joker for a Day Part 2
shortDescription: Joe, Murr, Q, and Sal take their crew by surprise again for another super-secret episode, sending brand new faces in front of the camera to compete in classic Impractical Jokers challenges.

title: Celebrating 200 Episodes: The First Hundred
subtitle: Celebrating 200 Episodes: The First Hundred
shortDescription: Join Joe, Murr, Q, and Sal as they reminisce about the first hundred episodes of Impractical Jokers!

title: Celebrating 200 Episodes: The Second Hundred
subtitle: Celebrating 200 Episodes: The Second Hundred
shortDescription: Join Joe, Murr, Q, and Sal as they reminisce about the past hundred episodes of Impractical Jokers!

title: Impractical Jokers: Slam Dunks
shortDescription: NBA stars Richard Jefferson and Channing Frye join Casey Jost to shoot hoops at Joe, Q, Murr and Sal's alma mater, Monsignor Farrell High School, and rate the guys performances of past seasons! Who will be named Jokers slam dunk champion?
